<task id="033" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-B-04 Migrate `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` action: populate outputSchema + node destination = workspace</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Schema-Aware Output</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>030, 031</dependencies>
    <blocks>040, 041, 048</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, seed, migration</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Data migration on existing production action; tags include `migration` (STANDARD per Step 3.5.5 decision tree); no code change; idempotency required.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B-G2</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches `sprk_analysisaction` row for `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` + the matching playbook node. Sibling tasks 032/034/035 migrate different rows in parallel — no overlap.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Populate the new `outputSchema` field on the existing
    `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` `sprk_analysisaction` row, and set the playbook
    node `destination = workspace` with `widgetType = StructuredOutputStreamWidget`. The
    outputSchema is derived from the action's current `$choices`-constrained output
    contract. R5 SC-18 surfaced the relevant rendering bugs for THIS action — the
    workspace surface is where `tldr: string[]` and `entities: { orgs, persons }`
    rendered as raw JSON. Declaring the schema here is the data foundation for tasks 040
    (array → bullets) + 041 (object → labeled key-value blocks).

    The migration script MUST be idempotent — guard with a GET before PATCH; if existing
    `sprk_outputschemajson` is non-null AND matches, skip; if mismatches, FAIL loudly with a
    conflict message. Same pattern for the node-level `destination = workspace` change.

    No BFF code changes here. This task seeds data only. The downstream
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (tasks 040 + 041) reads the populated outputSchema at
    render time and dispatches per-field-type formatting.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Familiar with the existing JPS pipeline + `$choices`
    output contract for `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1`, the scope library schema,
    the Dataverse Web API, and the `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` workspace surface.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_analysisaction` row for action code `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` has
    `sprk_outputschemajson` populated with a valid JSON Schema document covering all output
    fields (at minimum: `summary: string`, `tldr: string[]`, `entities: { organizations:
    string[], persons: string[] }` per R5 SC-18 evidence). The playbook node referencing
    this action has its `destination = workspace` and `widgetType =
    StructuredOutputStreamWidget`. Migration script committed + idempotent + applied to
    Spaarke Dev. Existing workspace summarization continues to render today's output
    (regression-checked; the widget is not YET schema-aware — that lands in tasks 040 +
    041).
  </goal>

